<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1657] Chrome browser sending OPTIONS method before POST in xmlHttpRequest</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1657</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per part of &quot;Preflighted requests&quot; chrome sends Options request to server to know what methods are allowed&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. But on server side(THttpServer.cpp), during reading header and parseStatusLine, we have handling for just POST, and hence request is not completed and server throws &quot;Bad Status (unsupported method): OPTIONS&quot; error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nczonline.net/blog/2010/05/25/cross-domain-ajax-with-cross-origin-resource-sharing/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nczonline.net/blog/2010/05/25/cross-domain-ajax-with-cross-origin-resource-sharing/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
